        <tr>
          <td>EMPL
            <a name="EMPL"> </a>
          </td>
          <td>Employer</td>
          <td>A legal entity that controls and directs a worker under an express or implied contract of employment and a salary or wages in compensation.

In worker&#x2019;s compensation cases, the Employer may be the &#x201C;organization&#x201D; responsible for paying the healthcare charges for employment related illness or injury.</td>
          <td>added v2.6</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>ORG
            <a name="ORG"> </a>
          </td>
          <td>Payee Organization</td>
          <td>The payee is not a person/individual/being, but an entity commonly identified as an organization.  Examples could be a country healthcare payer, or an insurance company responsible for payment.</td>
          <td>added v2.6</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>PERS
            <a name="PERS"> </a>
          </td>
          <td>Person</td>
          <td>A person/individual/being.</td>
          <td>added v2.6</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>PPER
            <a name="PPER"> </a>
          </td>
          <td>Pay Person</td>
          <td>Person/individual/being responsible for payment.</td>
          <td>added v2.6</td>
        </tr>
      </table>

    </div>
